text.section:
This section does not apply to an employee:
covered by a collective bargaining agreement or employment policy that includes shift breaks equal to or greater than those provided under this section;
exempt from overtime pay requirements under the Fair Labor Standards Act;
who works for a unit of the State, a county, or a municipality;
who works in a corporate office or other office location; or
who works for at least 4 consecutive hours for an employer at a single location with 5 or fewer employees.

section.section:
In determining the amount of any civil penalty to be imposed, the Commissioner shall consider the:
seriousness of the violation;
size of the employer's business;
employer's good faith in complying with this section; and
employer's history of violations under this section.
